					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13414788#post-4686535</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13414788/scp-5093#post-4686535</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 13 Jun 2020 07:51:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Raptie</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1968091</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>With a little bit more polish, you could end up with a masterpiece on your hands here. I really like the theme and characters and story here, but I feel like there's just a little something missing from the ending.</p> <p>Also, Cass's speech near the end feels kinda forced and unusually long-winded. Perhaps try paring it down to just a sentence or two.</p> <p>+1 overall, though!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13414788#post-4681438</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13414788/scp-5093#post-4681438</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2020 15:56:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DianaBerry</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3444428</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I was going to finish critiquing this but you uploaded it before I could, oh well. I feel like the dialogue was a bit forced and the anomaly itself was a bit unclear at times, but rather than that it’s a pretty solid article. I would have just suggested ways to make the story flow a little bit easier, and how to make the details clearer to the audience.</p> <p>Hesitant upvote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13414788#post-4681400</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13414788/scp-5093#post-4681400</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2020 15:24:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Its a Bad Idea</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3181609</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>You could have definitely gone farther into the themes presented here, but, as others have said, leaving this open-ended works as well.</p> <p>I also think the humanization of the D-class really makes this stand out amongst other exploration-oriented skips and definitely made it an enjoyable read.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
